The christening ceremony, held on Saturday in San Diego, was initially set to include Lewis himself, but he passed away from pancreatic cancer before the unveiling. Commemorating the civil rights icon, Woodward spoke about the ways in which Lewis’ legacy lives on. ‘John Lewis lives in all the spaces where people reach out their hands to pull others up to the lives that they deserve,’ she said.

Lewis, who served as the representative for Georgia’s 5th Congressional District for more than three decades, dedicated his life to fighting nonviolently for civil rights, insisting that ‘The vote is the most powerful nonviolent tool we have.’

Lewis fought alongside Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. throughout the Civil Rights movement, leading the 1965 voting rights march on the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma, AL, and surviving a brutal police beating that left him hospitalized.

Often seen as the moral conscience of Congress, he urged Americans to ‘get in good trouble, necessary trouble,’ in the fight for civil rights.

The 742-foot-long vessel named for Lewis is designed to refuel Navy carrier strike group ships operating at sea, according to the Navy.

‘Civil Service Mariners will operate this ship with the skill, resolve and courage displayed by John Lewis. With this ship, our naval service is better positioned to meet the challenges that lie ahead,’ said Rear Admiral Michael Wettlaufer, commander of Military Sealift Command.

The naming of the Navy ship is one of several tributes planned in honor of Lewis. The city of Atlanta unveiled a statue of Lewis in June; in Nashville, a stretch of Fifth Avenue was formally renamed after the Congressman; and nationwide, Americans gathered to hold vigils, marches, and celebrations to honor Lewis’ life and legacy.

#johnlewis #civilrights #usnavy #politics #legacy

node.title: U.S. Navy Names Ship After John Lewis

The christening ceremony, held on Saturday in San Diego, was initially set to include Lewis himself, but he passed away from pancreatic cancer before the unveiling. Commemorating the civil rights icon, Woodward spoke about the ways in which Lewis’ legacy lives on. ‘John Lewis lives in all the spaces where people reach out their hands to pull others up to the lives that they deserve,’ she said.

Lewis, who served as the representative for Georgia’s 5th Congressional District for more than three decades, dedicated his life to fighting nonviolently for civil rights, insisting that ‘The vote is the most powerful nonviolent tool we have.’

Lewis fought alongside Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. throughout the Civil Rights movement, leading the 1965 voting rights march on the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma, AL, and surviving a brutal police beating that left him hospitalized.

Often seen as the moral conscience of Congress, he urged Americans to ‘get in good trouble, necessary trouble,’ in the fight for civil rights.

The 742-foot-long vessel named for Lewis is designed to refuel Navy carrier strike group ships operating at sea, according to the Navy.

‘Civil Service Mariners will operate this ship with the skill, resolve and courage displayed by John Lewis. With this ship, our naval service is better positioned to meet the challenges that lie ahead,’ said Rear Admiral Michael Wettlaufer, commander of Military Sealift Command.

The naming of the Navy ship is one of several tributes planned in honor of Lewis. The city of Atlanta unveiled a statue of Lewis in June; in Nashville, a stretch of Fifth Avenue was formally renamed after the Congressman; and nationwide, Americans gathered to hold vigils, marches, and celebrations to honor Lewis’ life and legacy.

Ben & Jerry's announced on Monday that it will no longer sell its products in occupied Palestinian territories like the West Bank, saying that doing is 'inconsistent with our values.' The ice cream company, which is owned by parent company Unilever, said it will not be renewing its current license when it expires at the end of 2022. ⁠
⁠
Though @benandjerrys's will no longer be sold in occupied Palestine at that time, it reportedly will maintain a presence in Israel 'through a different arrangement,' per the brand. The company's announcement was criticized on social media by various Israeli leaders.⁠
⁠
This decision doesn't come entirely out of the blue, as Ben & Jerry's has previously forged a reputation as a socially conscious brand interested in progressive causes. In June 2020, just weeks after the murder of George Floyd, the company issued a statement calling on lawmakers to 'Defund the Police and Invest in Our Communities.' Months later, they released an ice cream flavor in tribute to Colin Kaepernick. They've also publicly criticized former President Donald Trump in the past, saying in November 2020 that the then-president 'sowed the seeds of division while waging an attack on the norms and values that define our democracy.'⁠
⁠
⁠

In a July 19 press release, Rep. Vern Buchanan (R-FL) revealed that he has tested positive for COVID-19, despite being fully vaccinated earlier this year. He is reportedly quarantining at home with ‘mild flu-like symptoms.’⁠
⁠
In a statement, he shared that he looks ‘forward to returning to work as soon as possible. In the meantime, this should serve as a reminder that although the vaccines provide a very high-degree of protection, we must remain vigilant in the fight against COVID-19.’⁠
The CDC says ‘a small percentage’ of people who are vaccinated will still contract the virus, but being vaccinated could prevent serious infections or symptoms.⁠
⁠
A year ago, Gary Tibbetts, an aide to Buchanan, died from the coronavirus at age 66. He was reportedly the first congressional staffer in the U.S. to pass away from the infection.⁠
⁠
⁠

node.text:
Paul Allard Hodgkins has been sentenced to 8 months in prison in association with the riot at the U.S. Capitol. Hodgkins is the first person to be sentenced in a felony case in connection with the January 6 riot. Hodgkins pleaded guilty to one count of obstructing, influencing, or impeding an ‘official proceeding.’⁠
⁠
Hodgkins traveled from Tampa, Florida, to Washington, D.C., where he ‘participated in’ the attack on the Capitol, prosecutors wrote in a sentencing memorandum. Hodgkins, carrying a red flag emblazoned with ‘Trump 2020,’ spent approximately 15 minutes in the Senate chamber, ’where he took ‘selfie-style’ photographs and saluted others who were shouting and cheering from a nearby raised platform in the well of the chamber.’⁠
⁠
The government had recommended 18 months in custody for Hodgkins because he ‘did not personally engage in or espouse violence or property destruction, he accepted responsibility early and in a fulsome manner, and he has taken significant steps toward his rehabilitation.’⁠
⁠
#january6th #capitolriots #politics #news

node.text:
5 Texas House Democrats who are fully vaccinated have tested positive for COVID-19 in Washington, D.C., as of Sunday. The lawmakers are part of a group of more than 50 Texas Democrats who fled the state on July 12 in order to block the passage of GOP-led voter suppression bills.⁠
⁠
While in D.C., the Texas Democrats have been meeting with federal lawmakers, including Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (D-NY), as well as Vice President Kamala Harris, to champion voting rights.⁠
⁠
According to a press release from the Texas House Democratic Caucus, ‘All of the HDC Members who tested positive are feeling good, with no symptoms or only mild symptoms.’ Caucus Chair Chris Turner called the positive tests a ‘sober reminder that COVID is still with us’ in a statement.⁠
⁠
⁠
